commit.message:
Retry service config fetch if it fails. (#80)

* Comply more thoroughly with WSGI spec

* Retry service config fetch if it fails.

add_all() used to directly fetch the service config and then either
construct the middleware or replace the app with a 503-serving
app. Now it will return an instance of ConfigFetchWrapper, which acts
as a WSGI middleware. If the service config has been loaded, it just
passes requests into the ordinary middleware and thence to the app.

But if the service config can't be loaded, it will retry. If threading
is available, it spawns a background thread to retry with exponential
backoff; if threading isn't available, it retries on every request.

Fixes #76.

commit.message:
Bump minor version (1.7.0 -> 1.9.0)

Rationale: x-http-method-override support (in 1.8.0)
and automatically detecting the latest config version if not
specified (in 1.9.0).

Determine ENDPOINTS_SERVICE_VERSION if not specified (#69)

In line with the java library if a user specifies ENDPOINTS_SERVICE_NAME
but not ENDPOINTS_SERVICE_VERSION we should assume that they want the
most recent version. This greatly simplifies the automatic deployment
scenario where we generate the API specification via endpoints framework
library and then immediately deploy the code.

Closes: #68

commit.message:
More gracefully handle errors loading service config

If we can't load service config, we'll loudly log it and then replace
the application with one which responds to all requests with HTTP 503
Service Unavailable.

Equivalent of https://github.com/cloudendpoints/endpoints-management-java/pull/39

Report API version in Report Requests. (#59)

This was a little awkward due to the way api versions are reported in
the service config, but this seems as reasonable as we're gonna get.

Rationale: oauth2client pin must be restored

Restore oauth2client 3.0.0 pin.

oauth2client 4.x.y uses the 'fasteners' package, which cannot run on App
Engine Standard.
